properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 11 at 8:42PM CST until February 13 at 10:00AM CST by NWS Lincoln IL
properties.description:
...SNOW TO SPREAD ACROSS AREAS NORTH OF I-70 ON WEDNESDAY...

.Precipitation will overspread much of central Illinois through
late morning into the afternoon, with rain possibly mixed with
sleet south of Interstate 70, while areas north of Interstate 70
should be mostly snow. Precipitation will continue Wednesday night
and into early Thursday, with snow accumulations of 3 to 4 inches
with some 5 inch amounts possible. Much colder air will move into
the area Thursday with some blowing snow possible.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 3 to 5
inches.

* WHERE...Portions of central and east central Illinois.

* WHEN...From 11 AM Wednesday to 10 AM CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions will impact the evening commute, with some
lingering slippery conditions and patchy blowing snow for the
Thursday morning commute.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for Illinois can be obtained on the
Internet at www.gettingaroundillinois.com.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 11 AM WEDNESDAY TO 10 AM CST THURSDAY
